         <LEFTI>
            <ECONOMIC_FINANCIAL_MIN_LEVEL>
               <P>LHC uses the following ratios to evaluate each Tenderer’s.</P>
               <P>Financial status:</P>
               <P>— turnover: this is calculated as double the typical value for projects called-off this framework. If a company’s turnover exceeds 400 000 GBP, then it passes this ratio,</P>
               <P>— profitability: this is calculated as profit after tax but before dividends and minority interests. If a company makes a profit, then it passes this ratio; and</P>
               <P>— liquidity: this is calculated as current assets and work in progress, divided by current liabilities. If the answer is greater than 1, then it passes this ratio. LHC may seek additional financial information from tenderers and or where applicable the Parent / Holding Company, and take this into consideration in the financial assessment.</P>
               <P>Further details are provided in the ITT Documentation.</P>
            </ECONOMIC_FINANCIAL_MIN_LEVEL>
